%% Bridge Pattern Class Diagram
%% Separates abstraction from implementation so both can vary independently

classDiagram
    class Abstraction {
        #implementor Implementor
        +Abstraction(Implementor)
        +operation() void
    }

    class RefinedAbstraction {
        +operation() void
        +extendedOperation() void
    }

    class Implementor {
        <<interface>>
        +operationImpl() void
    }

    class ConcreteImplementorA {
        +operationImpl() void
    }

    class ConcreteImplementorB {
        +operationImpl() void
    }

    class Client {
        +main() void
    }

    Abstraction <|-- RefinedAbstraction
    Abstraction --> Implementor : has
    Implementor <|.. ConcreteImplementorA
    Implementor <|.. ConcreteImplementorB
    Client --> Abstraction

    note for Abstraction "Abstraction hierarchy and\nImplementor hierarchy can\nvary independently."
